AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Event Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Event Type
AD_FIELD.HELP: Sets which of the 3 possible types the event is: *Close. This event is triggered by Cash Up process in case the payment type allows automatic movement of founds. It is used to determine the destination financial account for these movements. *In. Used by Cash Management process for deposits. When a deposit is done, the list of available In events for that payment type is shown to select one of them. Financial account in the event is used as origin account, this is, the amount will be taken from this account and deposited in the terminal's account. *Out. Used by Cash Management process for withdrawals. When a withdrawals is done, the list of available Out events for that payment type is shown to select one of them. Financial account in the event is used as destination account, this is, the amount will be taken from terminal's account and deposited on this account.
